        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-06-27 02:47:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 9:\n\n> LiWei, i included one of your ldiskfs OSD patch since this was required\n> for space accounting support. Please tell me if this is fine with you.\n\nNo problem at all.  However, make sure Alex's patch for ORI-132 is also included.  It would be even greater if you could change Alex's fix to restore \"current->fs->umask\" to its original value before returning from __osd_object_create().  Also, I would try adding\n\n  Test-Parameters: testlist=sanity envdefinitions=SLOW=yes\n\nor\n\n  Test-Parameters: testlist=sanity envdefinitions=ONLY=103\n\nto the commit message, so that sanity 103 would be run to verify this patch does not suffer from ORI-132.  (I haven't tried \"envdefinitions\" myself, but the lines above should result in an additional test session beside your normal \"review\" test session.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 9
    },
